criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. female aging from 30 to 70-year old;

          2. preoperative diagnosis of gynecologic malignancies;

          3. have the ability to comply with Research programs;

          4. voluntarily participate in the study and signed an informed consent form

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. patients with severe cardiovascular diseases, kidney, liver and other vital organs
             diseases, bone marrow disease and mental illness;

          2. patients suffering from autoimmune diseases;

          3. patients with acute infectious disease or infection early phase of infection;

          4. patients with urinary tract infection;

          5. patients with infection or erosion of ano-genital skin;

          6. for any other reason, the researchers considered unsuitable for inclusion.
